<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="21" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,151,680]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,620,645]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name is derived from the Latin 
<emphasis box="[857,952,620,645]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">hamatus</emphasis>
, meaning hooked, referring to the hooked distal half of the uncus lobe.
</paragraph>
